I'm back for a few days before hopping on the road again - another ~1,500 miles down in the last few days, and a lot more of America seen. I'm exhausted! But not too exhausted to share more of the Waldo Hotel, one of the most elegant hotels ever constructed in West Virginia. Although it has taken on significant damage through neglect - largely via the usual suspect, water - it is still in excellent condition and a great candidate for rehab. Here's hoping that this is its future, instead of the alternative - demolition - which has already been suggested...﻿

I'm on my way to PDX to hang out with +Brian Matiash and friends for a few days. This is a "map selfie" at a rest-stop along I-5. :)
It's such a gorgeous day, I hate spending it in a car ... maybe Brian will let me run around and frolic in a park once we get to Portland? :) Although I guess I did already get some running in on my workout this morning (and I PR'd with my dead-lift ... 155lbs, boo-yah!)﻿

On the road again....
In a few hours I'm jumping on a plane for a 10 day trip to Granada, Nicaragua. Don't really know what the internet situation will be where I'm going... but I know that I probably won't be uploading any new images until I get back.
Before I got out the door... I wanted to post a little something for #Caturday hosted by +Lee Daniels and +Christophe Friedli @ +CATURDAY!. This was taken a few years back in Old San Juan, Puerto Rico. There is a beautiful path that runs for a mile or so In front of the old fort walls called (appropriately) the Catwalk. It is the home to many, many stray cats that will come to greet you as you stroll. A great place for a cat lover to walk!
